'''Mert Müldür''' (born 3 April 1999) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right-back]] or a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]]. Born in Austria, he represents the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]]. A versatile player, he is capable of playing in multiple positions, especially as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]].

==Club career==
=== Rapid Wien ===
Müldür joined the [[SK Rapid Wien]] youth academy at the age of six in 2006, and worked his way up into the professional team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skrapid.at/de/startseite/news/news/aktuelles/2016/06/gruen-weisses-bekenntnis-u18-spieler-mert-muelduer-unterschreibt/|title=Grün-Weißes Bekenntnis: U18-Spieler Mert Müldür unterschreibt|website=SK Rapid}}</ref> He made his professional debut for SK Rapid in a 4–1 [[Austrian Football Bundesliga]] loss to [[FC Red Bull Salzburg]] on 13 May 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kicker.de/rapid-wien-gegen-salzburg-2018-bundesliga-oesterreich-3819849/schema|title=Schema: Rapid Wien - RB Salzburg - tipico - Bundesliga, Saison 2017/18, 34. Spieltag|first=kicker, Nürnberg|last=Germany|website=kicker}}</ref> On 29 May 2018, Müldür signed his first professional contract for three years with Rapid Wien.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skrapid.at/en/home/news/news/latest-news/2018/05/mert-muelduer-earns-professional-contract/|title=Mert Müldür earns professional contract|website=SK Rapid}}</ref>

=== Sassuolo ===
On 20 August 2019, Müldür signed for Italian club [[U.S. Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]]. He made his debut five days later, coming on as a [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a 2–1 away loss against [[Torino FC|Torino]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sassuolocalcio.it/articles/?id=9&aid=5405|title=Calciomercato: il Sassuolo ingaggia Mert Müldür dal Rapid Vienna|website=www.sassuolocalcio.it}}</ref>

On 15 August 2022, he suffered an ankle fracture injury against [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] and missed 16 matches.

=== Fenerbahçe ===
On 2 August 2023, Müldür signed a four-year contract with Fenerbahçe until 2027.<ref>{{cite web |title=Fenerbahçemize hoş geldin Mert Müldür |url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2023/8/fenerbahcemize-hos-geldin-mert-muldur |website=fenerbahce.org |access-date=2 August 2023 |language=tr |date=2 August 2023}}</ref>

He made his debut with the team in a 3–0 [[UEFA Conference League|UEFA Europa Conference League]] win over [[NK Maribor]] on 17 August 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2023/8/fenerbahcemiz-uefa-avrupa-konferans-ligi-nde-play-off-turuna-yukseldi|title=Fenerbahçemiz, UEFA Avrupa Konferans Ligi’nde Play-off turuna yükseldi|website=fenerbahce.org}}</ref> On 21 August 2023, he made his [[Süper Lig]] debut with the team against [[Samsunspor]] in an away game, Fenerbahçe won 2–0.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2023/8/yilport-samsunspor-0-2-fenerbahce | title=Yılport Samsunspor 0-2 Fenerbahçe }}</ref>

On 2 February 2026, he made his 100th appearances in all competitions for Fenerbahçe against [[FCSB]] in 1–1 [[2025–26 UEFA Europa League#League phase|UEFA Europa League]] away draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2026/1/fcsb-1-1-fenerbahce|title=FCSB 1–1 Fenerbahçe|date=29 January 2025|accessdate=3 February 2026|website=fenerbahce.org|language=tr}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Austria to Turkish parents, Müldür is a youth international for Turkey.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kurier.at/sport/fussball/rapid-mert-muelduer-erhaelt-einen-profi-vertrag/400042762|title=Rapid: Mert Müldür erhält einen Profi-Vertrag|publisher=}}</ref> He made his debut for the senior [[Turkey national football team|Turkish national team]] on 11 October 2018 in a 0–0 [[Exhibition game|friendly]] draw against [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=528&macId=205352|title=TURKEY BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA - Match Details TFF|website=www.tff.org}}.</ref>

At [[UEFA Euro 2024]], Turkey's first and last goals were ignominiously credited to Müldür: he began his country's goal tally with a [[Volley (association football)|volley]] against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]] in the group stage opener<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036171--turkiye-vs-georgia/|title=TURKEY GEORGIA - Match Details|website=[[UEFA]]}}</ref> and scored the decisive [[Own goal#Association football|own goal]] against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] in the quarter-finals.

==Style of play==
Müldür is right-footed and began playing for [[SK Rapid Wien|Rapid Wien II]] as a right-back, although he is also known to play in the left-back position and as an attacker. Müldür is known for his sliding tackles, speed, stamina and aerial abilities which can make him play in a centre-back position. Through utilization of both feet, he can also successfully distribute passes from the back, which is considered an important feature of the new generation of defenders.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.goal.com/tr/haber/mert-muelduer-kimdir/1kj5sjn7fo3ej10mwuehveoa5x |title=Fenerbahçe ve Beşiktaş'ın ilgilendiği Mert Müldür kimdir? |website=GOAL.com |date=5 September 2018 |access-date=2 December 2024 |language=tr}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Müldür is a longtime fan of [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] since his childhood.<ref>{{cite news |title=Galatasaray'ı değil çocukluk aşkını seçti |url=https://www.haberet.com/spor/mert-muldur-fenerbahcede-galatasarayi-degil-cocukluk-askini-secti-34558 |website=haberet.com |access-date=31 July 2023 |language=tr}}</ref>

Müldür is [[multilingualism|multilingual]], speaking five languages fluently: [[Turkish language|Turkish]] and [[German language|German]] as main languages, [[English language|English]] in education, also [[Bosnian language|Bosnian]] and [[Serbian language|Serbian]] fluently because of his Serbian girlfriend, whom he has been with for many years.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.fanatik.com.tr/fenerbahce/mert-muldurun-sevgilisi-koprena-andjela-panik-oldu-kalbimin-durdugu-yer-2542586 |title=Mert Müldür'ün sevgilisi Koprena Andjela panik oldu: Kalbimin durduğu yer |website=Fanatik |date=18 March 2024 |access-date=25 November 2024 |language=tr}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cnnturk.com/magazin/galeri/galler-turkiye-maci-oncesi-gundem-oldu-mert-muldurun-sevgilisi-koprena-andjeladan-kick-boks-sov-turkiyenin-gonlunu-fethetti-2150245?page=5 |title=A Milli Takım'ın yıldızı Mert Müldür’ün sevgilisi Koprena Andjela'dan kick boks şov! 'TÜRKİYE'NİN GÖNLÜNÜ FETHETTİ!' |website=CNN Türk |date=7 September 2024 |access-date=25 November 2024 |language=tr}}</ref>

